eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has the details. #eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Eighty-four health facilities have been affected by the floods in KwaZulu-Natal. It will cost at least R184m to repair them. Water tankers and mobile structures are being rolled out in the meantime. Health Minister Joe Phahla, his deputy Sibongiseni Dhlomo, and the province's Health MEC Nomagugu Simelame-Zulu assessed the scale of flood damage in and around Inanda and the eThekwini municipality. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has the details in the video above.